  "text": "Expression analyses suggest that both Pdgfra and Kit, but not Abl1, genes are expressed in PrE and in XEN cells [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , indicating that Kit is not required for the establishment or maintenance of XEN cells (Fig. 4A) . Furthermore, Kit W-lacZ/W-lacZ XEN cells proliferated at a similar rate to wild-type XEN cells in serum and serum-free culture conditions (data not shown). To determine whether we could recapitulate the mitogenic effect of Gleevec in the absence of KIT signaling, Kit-deficient XEN cells were cultured in the presence of Gleevec (Fig. 4B) . Their proliferation was comparable to that of wild-type XEN cells.",
